\taxon{construction}
\title{join}

\p{
The join of two types, #{A} and #{B}, is given by the pushout of #{(A \leftarrow A \times B \rightarrow B)}. It's usually denoted #{A * B}.
}

\p{
The universal property of push-out classifies maps out of the join as:
##{
    (A * B \to C) \simeq \Sigma_{(f : A \to C)} \Sigma_{(g : B \to C)} (\Pi_{(a : A), (b : B)} f(a) = g(b)) 
}
}